[{"location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Public","page":"API","title":"Public","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.AbstractCoordinateSystem","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.AbstractCoordinateSystem","text":"AbstractCoordinateSystem\n\nBase abstract type for all coordinate system implementations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.AbstractCoordinateVector","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.AbstractCoordinateVector","text":"AbstractCoordinateVector\n\nBase abstract type to represent coordinates in a coordinate systems.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.AbstractDataVariable","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.AbstractDataVariable","text":"A variable v of a type derived from AbstractDataVariable should at least implement:\n\nBase.parent(v): the parent array of the variable\n\nOptional:\n\ntimes(v): the timestamps of the variable\nunits(v): the units of the variable\nmeta(v): the metadata of the variable\nname(v): the name of the variable\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.DataSet","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.DataSet","text":"DataSet <: AbstractDataSet\n\nA concrete dataset with a name, data (parameters), and metadata.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.DataSet-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.DataSet","text":"Construct a DataSet from a name and data, with optional metadata.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.DataSet-Tuple{LDataSet}","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.DataSet","text":"DataSet(ld::LDataSet; kwargs...)\n\nCreate a concrete DataSet from a Dataset template with specified data.\n\nSee also: LDataSet\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.Instrument","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.Instrument","text":"Instrument <: AbstractInstrument\n\nFields\n\nname: The name of the instrument\nmetadata: Additional metadata\ndatasets: Collection of datasets\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.Instrument-Tuple{Dict}","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.Instrument","text":"Construct an Instrument from a dictionary.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.Instrument-Tuple{}","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.Instrument","text":"keyword-based constructor\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.LDataSet","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.LDataSet","text":"LDataSet <: AbstractDataSet\n\nA template for generating datasets with parameterized naming patterns.\n\nFields\n\nformat: Format string pattern for the dataset name\ndata: Dictionary of variable patterns\nmetadata: Additional metadata\n\nExamples\n\nusing SPEDAS.MMS\n\n# Access FPI dataset specification\nlds = mms.datasets.fpi_moms\n\n# Create a concrete dataset with specific parameters\nds = DataSet(lds; probe=1, data_rate=\"fast\", data_type=\"des\")\n\nThe format string and variable patterns use placeholders like {probe}, {data_rate},  which are replaced with actual values when creating a concrete DataSet.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.LDataSet-Tuple{Dict}","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.LDataSet","text":"Construct a LDataSet from a dictionary.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.Project","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.Project","text":"Project <: AbstractProject\n\nA representation of a project or mission containing instruments and datasets.\n\nFields\n\nname: The name of the project\nmetadata: Additional metadata\ninstruments: Collection of instruments\ndatasets: Collection of datasets\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.Project-Tuple{}","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.Project","text":"keyword-based constructor\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.abbr-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.abbr","text":"abbr(p)\n\nGet the abbreviation (abbr) of p.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.getcsys-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.getcsys","text":"getcsys(x)\n\nGet the coordinate system of x.\n\nIf x is a instance of AbstractCoordinateSystem, return x itself. If x is a type of AbstractCoordinateSystem, return an instance of the coordinate system, i.e. x().\n\nThis is a generic function, packages should extend it for their own types.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#Private","page":"API","title":"Private","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Base.:∘-Tuple{Any, AbstractProduct}","page":"API","title":"Base.:∘","text":"Create a new product with the composed function\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel._getfield","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel._getfield","text":"_getfield(v, name, default)\n\nReturn the field from a composite v for the given name, or the given default if no field is present.\n\nSee also: getfield.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SpaceDataModel.is_doy-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","title":"SpaceDataModel.is_doy","text":"Check if a string is in Day of Year format (YYYY-DDD).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"interface/#Interface","page":"Interface","title":"Interface","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"interface/","page":"Interface","title":"Interface","text":"SpaceDataModel.jl provides a set of abstractions and generic functions that can be extended by users to create custom implementations. This page documents these interfaces and provides examples of how to use them.","category":"page"},{"location":"interface/#References","page":"Interface","title":"References","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"interface/","page":"Interface","title":"Interface","text":"DataAPI.jl: A data-focused namespace for packages to share functions","category":"page"},{"location":"interface/#Coordinate-Systems","page":"Interface","title":"Coordinate Systems","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"interface/","page":"Interface","title":"Interface","text":"The package exports three key components for coordinate system handling:","category":"page"},{"location":"interface/","page":"Interface","title":"Interface","text":"AbstractCoordinateSystem: Base abstract type for all coordinate system implementations\nAbstractCoordinateVector: Base abstract type to represent coordinates in a coordinate systems\ngetcsys: Function to retrieve the coordinate system from an object","category":"page"},{"location":"interface/","page":"Interface","title":"Interface","text":"There are two main approaches to implementing coordinate vectors and their associated systems:","category":"page"},{"location":"interface/#Approach-1:-Explicit-Coordinate-System-Field","page":"Interface","title":"Approach 1: Explicit Coordinate System Field","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"interface/","page":"Interface","title":"Interface","text":"Store the coordinate system directly as a field in the vector type:","category":"page"},{"location":"interface/","page":"Interface","title":"Interface","text":"# Define a coordinate system\nstruct GEO <: AbstractCoordinateSystem end\n\n# Define a vector with an explicit coordinate system field\nstruct CoordinateVector{D, T} <: AbstractCoordinateVector\n    data::D\n    csys::T\nend\n\n# Implementation of getcsys simply returns the stored field\ngetcsys(x::CoordinateVector) = x.csys","category":"page"},{"location":"interface/#Approach-2:-Implicit-Coordinate-System","page":"Interface","title":"Approach 2: Implicit Coordinate System","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"interface/","page":"Interface","title":"Interface","text":"Associate a specific coordinate system with a vector type:","category":"page"},{"location":"interface/","page":"Interface","title":"Interface","text":"# Define a coordinate system\nstruct GEO <: AbstractCoordinateSystem end\n\n# Define a vector type specific to a coordinate system\nstruct GEOVector{D} <: AbstractCoordinateVector\n    data::D\nend\n\n# Implementation of getcsys returns the appropriate system\ngetcsys(x::GEOVector) = GEO()","category":"page"},{"location":"interface/","page":"Interface","title":"Interface","text":"Both approaches are highly efficient and provide equivalent performance due to Julia's type inference system.","category":"page"},{"location":"interface/#Elsewhere","page":"Interface","title":"Elsewhere","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"interface/","page":"Interface","title":"Interface","text":"CoordRefSystems.jl provides conversions between Coordinate Reference Systems (CRS) for cartography use cases.\nGeodesy.jl for working with points in various world and local coordinate systems.\nWCS.jl : Astronomical World Coordinate System library ","category":"page"},{"location":"#SpaceDataModel.jl","page":"Home","title":"SpaceDataModel.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"SpaceDataModel.jl is a lightweight Julia package providing a flexible data model for handling space/heliospheric science data. It offers abstractions for organizing space data into hierarchical structures including projects, instruments, datasets, and data variables.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"It is used in SPEDAS.jl, Speasy.jl, and HAPIClient.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(\"SpaceDataModel\")","category":"page"},{"location":"#Usage","page":"Home","title":"Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using SpaceDataModel\n\n# Create a project\nproject = Project(; name=\"Project Name\")\ninstrument = Instrument(; name=\"Instrument Name\")\ndataset = DataSet(name=\"Dataset Name\")\n\npush!(project, instrument, dataset)\npush!(instrument, dataset)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"See Data Model and Project Module - SPEDAS.jl for more details.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Features","page":"Home","title":"Features","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Hierarchical organization of data (projects, instruments, datasets)\nPretty printing for data inspection","category":"page"},{"location":"#Reference","page":"Home","title":"Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"SPASE Model\nHAPI Data Access Specification\nCommonDataModel.jl contains abstracts type definition for loading and manipulating GRIB, NetCDF, geoTiff and Zarr files.\nNetCDF Data Model","category":"page"}]
